    <body>
      <section eId="sec_27_2615">
        <num>27-2615</num>
        <heading>Department responsibilities</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_2615__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>maintain a list of manufacturers who are\nregistered pursuant to section 27-2605 of this title,</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_2615__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>maintain a\nlist of each such manufacturer's brands, and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_2615__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>post such lists on the\ndepartment's website.\n  3. The department may waive the recycling surcharge payable by a\nmanufacturer under this title when the manufacturer demonstrates in an\napplication to the department it was unable to accept the weight of\nelectronic waste required by section 27-2603 of this title despite the\nmanufacturer's best efforts. The application shall be made with the\nannual report required by section 27-2617 of this title. The application\nshall include such information as the department requires. A waiver\nprovided pursuant to this subdivision shall not relieve a manufacturer\nfrom the obligation to comply with the provisions of this title not\nspecifically addressed in such waiver.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
